1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,255
[soft traditional music playing]

2
00:00:07,966 --> 00:00:09,634
[Jalil] <i>I'm going to set things right.</i>

3
00:00:09,718 --> 00:00:12,721
<i>I'm sure Father is innocent.</i>

4
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,351
[Marcus] <i>The person who killed</i>
<i>Oliver and the others</i>

5
00:00:18,435 --> 00:00:20,478
<i>was highly trained and skilled.</i>

6
00:00:20,562 --> 00:00:21,312
I fought him myself.

7
00:00:21,396 --> 00:00:22,814
[Marcus] <i>This is no ordinary group,</i>

8
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:26,192
<i>and they won't stop</i>
<i>until they erase all the evidence.</i>

9
00:00:26,276 --> 00:00:28,111
<i>I know who their next target is.</i>

10
00:00:28,194 --> 00:00:29,362
<i>Datu Rahman.</i>

11
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:34,409
<i>They manipulated us into bringing</i>
<i>Datu Rahman to Manila.</i>

12
00:00:34,909 --> 00:00:36,703
<i>Now, they will find a way</i>

13
00:00:36,786 --> 00:00:39,289
<i>to take him from our custody.</i>

14
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:41,875
‪[tense music playing]

15
00:00:41,958 --> 00:00:44,919
[activists] We want justice!
We want justice!

16
00:00:47,255 --> 00:00:49,090
[activists] Justice for him!

17
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,384
- [man] Stop!
- [gunshots]

18
00:00:53,303 --> 00:00:54,846
[Mia] <i>Where is Datu Rahman?! Where is he?</i>

19
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:56,765
<i>I said, where is Datu Rahman?!</i>

20
00:00:57,640 --> 00:00:58,975
[Marcus] <i>If my instincts are correct,</i>

21
00:00:59,059 --> 00:01:00,894
<i>this transfer is not about security.</i>

22
00:01:00,977 --> 00:01:02,896
<i>In reality, it's an execution.</i>

23
00:01:03,480 --> 00:01:06,274
[grunting]

24
00:01:06,357 --> 00:01:08,276
- [Datu] <i>Jalil!</i>
- [electricity zapping]

25
00:01:09,277 --> 00:01:10,779
[Jalil] Father!

26
00:01:11,863 --> 00:01:12,947
[grunting and groaning]

27
00:01:13,031 --> 00:01:15,325
[tires screeching]

28
00:01:17,202 --> 00:01:19,704
[rapid gunfire]

29
00:01:20,872 --> 00:01:23,541
[Rahman] Just who are you people?
Get your hands off me!

30
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:25,752
- [Datu] Let me go!
- [man grunts]

31
00:01:28,838 --> 00:01:30,048
[Jalil] Father!

32
00:01:34,219 --> 00:01:36,137
[heavy breathing]

33
00:01:37,055 --> 00:01:40,475
[mysterious theme music playing]

34
00:01:52,195 --> 00:01:53,822
[suspenseful music playing]

35
00:01:54,405 --> 00:01:56,157
All units, cover all possible exits!

36
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:57,450
[Lara] <i>Datu Rahman must be located!</i>

37
00:01:57,534 --> 00:01:58,827
- [radio crackles]
- [hurried footsteps]

38
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,540
- [Usman] Find him!
- [cop 1, cop 2] Yes, sir!

39
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:10,547
[suspenseful music continues]

40
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,632
Where are you, Datu Rahman?

41
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:19,013
Have you seen an old man
in a vest and detainee's shirt?

42
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:21,057
- He's Muslim.
- [woman 1] No, sorry.

43
00:02:23,685 --> 00:02:27,063
Excuse me, miss! Have you seen an old man
in a vest and detainee's shirt?

44
00:02:27,147 --> 00:02:29,899
- He's Muslim. Have you?
- [woman 2] I haven't. Sorry.

45
00:02:31,734 --> 00:02:34,404
[tires screeching]

46
00:02:38,408 --> 00:02:40,660
Datu Rahman… Where are you?

47
00:02:44,664 --> 00:02:47,041
[tires screeching]

48
00:02:51,754 --> 00:02:53,756
[gunshots]

49
00:02:55,717 --> 00:02:57,218
[grunting and groaning]

50
00:02:57,844 --> 00:02:59,012
[gunshot]

51
00:03:02,724 --> 00:03:04,142
[gunshots]

52
00:03:05,310 --> 00:03:06,144
[Datu Rahman] Let me go!

53
00:03:07,145 --> 00:03:08,646
- [thwacking]
- [whimpering]

54
00:03:08,730 --> 00:03:09,731
[labored breathing]

55
00:03:11,065 --> 00:03:12,317
[Datu Rahman grunting]

56
00:03:13,484 --> 00:03:14,652
[gunshots]

57
00:03:20,116 --> 00:03:21,451
[gunshots]

58
00:03:24,537 --> 00:03:25,955
[rapid gunfire in distance]

59
00:03:38,426 --> 00:03:41,471
[hurried footsteps]

60
00:03:43,973 --> 00:03:44,849
Hey!

61
00:03:46,017 --> 00:03:48,228
[music becomes tense]

62
00:03:58,738 --> 00:04:00,073
[both grunting]

63
00:04:01,115 --> 00:04:02,283
He was their leader.

64
00:04:02,367 --> 00:04:04,702
<i>The very same man who captured Father.</i>

65
00:04:06,829 --> 00:04:08,498
[siren wailing]

66
00:04:14,128 --> 00:04:15,421
Marcus!

67
00:04:22,136 --> 00:04:23,346
Remaining units,

68
00:04:23,429 --> 00:04:26,099
find Datu Rahman
before he escapes for good!

69
00:04:29,185 --> 00:04:33,022
[stirring music playing]

70
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:55,146
[loud thud]

71
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:14,874
[music becomes unsettling]

72
00:06:22,715 --> 00:06:24,926
[footsteps receding]

73
00:06:36,938 --> 00:06:39,941
[music becomes suspenseful]

74
00:06:48,574 --> 00:06:51,911
[breathing heavily]

75
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,914
- [panting]
- [birds chirping]

76
00:06:54,997 --> 00:06:56,833
[chicken clucking]

77
00:07:01,796 --> 00:07:05,716
[music fading]

78
00:07:05,800 --> 00:07:09,804
[dark music playing]

79
00:07:16,519 --> 00:07:19,564
[breathing heavily]

80
00:07:31,909 --> 00:07:34,287
[breathing anxiously]

81
00:07:35,872 --> 00:07:39,292
- [dogs barking]
- [hurried footsteps]

82
00:07:39,375 --> 00:07:42,879
[panting]

83
00:07:42,962 --> 00:07:45,047
[dogs barking]

84
00:07:45,131 --> 00:07:46,632
[Jalil] Father, where are you?

85
00:07:48,301 --> 00:07:49,302
[voice breaks] Where are you?

86
00:07:49,385 --> 00:07:52,430
[breathing heavily]

87
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:58,603
[suspenseful music playing]

88
00:08:01,355 --> 00:08:03,232
I need visuals on Datu Rahman! Right now!

89
00:08:04,692 --> 00:08:06,652
- Lara! Lara…
- What are you doing here?

90
00:08:06,736 --> 00:08:08,321
I saw the ones who took Datu Rahman.

91
00:08:08,404 --> 00:08:09,864
They were all wearing masks.

92
00:08:09,947 --> 00:08:12,241
I crossed paths with them,
but they had guns.

93
00:08:12,325 --> 00:08:14,368
My God, what were you thinking?
Do you have a death wish?

94
00:08:14,452 --> 00:08:15,661
Lara, listen.

95
00:08:15,745 --> 00:08:18,080
There was a man running
after Datu Rahman's captors.

96
00:08:18,164 --> 00:08:19,165
A man.

97
00:08:19,248 --> 00:08:20,374
Have you identified him?

98
00:08:21,083 --> 00:08:24,045
No. But whoever that man is,
we have to track him down first.

99
00:08:24,128 --> 00:08:25,546
No! You're suspended!

100
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:27,465
You're not even supposed to be here!

101
00:08:27,548 --> 00:08:29,425
Lara, I can't drop everything
just because--

102
00:08:29,509 --> 00:08:30,760
Do you even hear yourself?

103
00:08:30,843 --> 00:08:33,054
Of everyone I know, you're the one
who always follows the rules!

104
00:08:33,137 --> 00:08:34,263
[Marcus] And where did it get me, Lara?

105
00:08:34,347 --> 00:08:36,599
Where did that get me?
A lot of people have died!

106
00:08:36,682 --> 00:08:39,310
Innocent people, my entire group…
They were all killed!

107
00:08:39,393 --> 00:08:41,270
I need to find out the truth,

108
00:08:41,354 --> 00:08:43,564
so I can give justice to Russel, Harold--

109
00:08:43,648 --> 00:08:44,607
Marcus.

110
00:08:44,690 --> 00:08:45,858
[somber music playing]

111
00:08:45,942 --> 00:08:48,194
Datu Rahman is a loose end in all of this.

112
00:08:48,277 --> 00:08:49,612
Nothing here is a coincidence, Lara.

113
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:51,656
I know. And I believe you.

114
00:08:51,739 --> 00:08:54,951
That's why we tried so hard
to protect him.

115
00:08:55,034 --> 00:08:57,828
Lara, they are always
one step ahead of us.

116
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:00,331
It was all a setup! Believe me!

117
00:09:00,414 --> 00:09:02,083
They're going to kill Datu Rahman,

118
00:09:02,166 --> 00:09:04,669
and once he's gone,
the truth dies with him.

119
00:09:04,752 --> 00:09:06,921
So I need to find him as soon as possible.

120
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:08,548
Marcus, we both want the same thing.

121
00:09:08,631 --> 00:09:10,550
But unlike you, I am not suspended.

122
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:12,677
If Director Azuelo finds out about this,

123
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:14,637
you'll be terminated
from service without question.

124
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,556
I don't care anymore, Lara.

125
00:09:17,306 --> 00:09:19,725
Right now, I need to do the right thing.

126
00:09:19,809 --> 00:09:23,104
[dramatic music playing]

127
00:09:40,371 --> 00:09:42,748
[reporter 1] <i>The entire country</i>
<i>is in an anxious state</i>

128
00:09:42,832 --> 00:09:46,043
<i>following the news</i>
<i>of the incident during the transfer</i>

129
00:09:46,127 --> 00:09:49,463
<i>of high-value detainee</i>
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar.</i>

130
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:52,550
[reporter 2] <i>The operation</i>
<i>descended into chaos</i>

131
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,386
<i>when activists and sympathizers</i>

132
00:09:55,469 --> 00:09:57,972
<i>swarmed his convoy route,</i>

133
00:09:58,055 --> 00:10:00,600
<i>ultimately leading to his escape.</i>

134
00:10:00,683 --> 00:10:04,061
[reporter 3] <i>Criticisms</i>
<i>are being directed at the NLEA,</i>

135
00:10:04,145 --> 00:10:06,147
<i>particularly</i>
<i>the Special Intelligence Division,</i>

136
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:07,607
<i>over the disappearance of the suspect.</i>

137
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:09,150
<i>In the world of social media,</i>

138
00:10:09,233 --> 00:10:11,944
<i>countless voices</i>
<i>are demanding accountability.</i>

139
00:10:12,028 --> 00:10:14,739
[reporter 4] Sir, how was
Datu Rahman able to escape?

140
00:10:14,822 --> 00:10:16,949
Was there a failure
of security on your part?

141
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:21,454
Just great. These cops
really are incompetent.

142
00:10:21,537 --> 00:10:23,414
[reporter 5] <i>What do you say</i>
<i>to those blaming you for this,</i>

143
00:10:23,497 --> 00:10:26,000
<i>and more specifically for the massacre</i>
<i>in the Muslim community?</i>

144
00:10:26,083 --> 00:10:28,002
[reporter 6] <i>Sir, many are alarmed</i>

145
00:10:28,085 --> 00:10:30,129
<i>by the escape of the suspected criminal.</i>

146
00:10:30,212 --> 00:10:32,256
<i>How do you plan to recapture him?</i>

147
00:10:32,340 --> 00:10:36,886
Our security was structured
and well-coordinated.

148
00:10:36,969 --> 00:10:39,513
<i>It just so happened</i>
<i>that Datu Rahman Abubakar</i>

149
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:42,016
<i>was a very cunning and dangerous person.</i>

150
00:10:42,099 --> 00:10:46,228
<i>That's why, even though</i>
<i>the NLEA and the SID</i>

151
00:10:46,896 --> 00:10:49,440
<i>were deployed in full force to guard him,</i>

152
00:10:49,982 --> 00:10:51,817
<i>he still managed to get away.</i>

153
00:10:51,901 --> 00:10:55,363
[gloomy music playing]

154
00:10:57,198 --> 00:11:01,202
One person said, "The SID and NLEA
keep failing, time after time."

155
00:11:01,285 --> 00:11:04,497
Another said, "You people
are so reckless! Shame on you!"

156
00:11:05,081 --> 00:11:06,415
A third one said,
"They kill innocent people.

157
00:11:06,499 --> 00:11:09,251
They'd probably kill Datu Rahman, too."

158
00:11:10,252 --> 00:11:11,962
Wow, the things people are saying.

159
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:13,089
[soft thud]

160
00:11:13,172 --> 00:11:14,423
[Felix] You know,

161
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:18,469
criminals like Datu Rahman

162
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:20,763
deserve to be shot down.

163
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:21,806
Domingo!

164
00:11:22,973 --> 00:11:23,891
What's wrong, ma'am?

165
00:11:25,184 --> 00:11:28,145
We're the victims here, aren't we?

166
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:29,897
All I'm saying

167
00:11:29,980 --> 00:11:32,983
is that I want a world free of crime.

168
00:11:33,067 --> 00:11:34,985
Where no one hurts anyone. That's all.

169
00:11:38,447 --> 00:11:39,490
[Felix sighs]

170
00:11:43,119 --> 00:11:48,916
[music intensifying]

171
00:11:52,711 --> 00:11:55,881
[gloomy music playing]

172
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:59,885
[Azuelo] <i>Based on our investigation,</i>

173
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:05,182
<i>Datu Rahman Abubakar was conspiring</i>

174
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:10,312
<i>with his accomplices in the syndicate</i>
<i>and select civilians</i>

175
00:12:10,813 --> 00:12:12,523
<i>to incite a riot,</i>

176
00:12:13,315 --> 00:12:15,192
<i>an event enabling his escape from the law.</i>

177
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:16,694
[reporters clamoring]

178
00:12:16,777 --> 00:12:19,822
[tense music playing]

179
00:12:19,905 --> 00:12:22,366
[overlapping shouting]

180
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:23,868
Liar.

181
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:28,539
Datu Rahman did not escape.

182
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:29,999
[breathes deeply]

183
00:12:30,624 --> 00:12:32,376
- [brakes squealing]
- [man] There's Marcus Reyes!

184
00:12:32,460 --> 00:12:33,919
Open fire on him!

185
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:43,387
- [engine revving]
- [tires screeching]

186
00:12:51,645 --> 00:12:53,606
[Teresa] Marcus? Where are you going?

187
00:12:54,273 --> 00:12:58,027
You'll put yourself in even more danger
without the protection of your badge.

188
00:12:58,611 --> 00:12:59,862
Ma, I need to do this.

189
00:12:59,945 --> 00:13:01,906
[inhales, exhales deeply]

190
00:13:01,989 --> 00:13:02,865
Son!

191
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:12,166
I thought I could bring
Father back safely.

192
00:13:13,709 --> 00:13:16,212
But then those men found us.

193
00:13:17,963 --> 00:13:19,924
Now it feels like I handed
Father over to them.

194
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:25,012
What about that Marcus Reyes?

195
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,598
Is he involved
in your father’s disappearance?

196
00:13:31,685 --> 00:13:34,396
[rapid gunfire]

197
00:13:35,773 --> 00:13:38,067
[gunshots]

198
00:13:38,817 --> 00:13:41,570
He also went after the men
who took Father.

199
00:13:42,613 --> 00:13:46,242
His team was killed on the island.

200
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,285
I think…

201
00:13:48,369 --> 00:13:50,746
I think he just wanted
Father back in prison.

202
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:54,667
What could be the motive
of the people who took your father?

203
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:57,836
I don't know!

204
00:13:59,296 --> 00:14:00,673
All I know is,

205
00:14:01,173 --> 00:14:04,468
the longer Father remains missing,
the more danger he’ll be in.

206
00:14:08,389 --> 00:14:09,640
[knocking]

207
00:14:16,272 --> 00:14:17,106
[Jamillah] Uncle Omar.

208
00:14:19,608 --> 00:14:20,943
Jamillah.

209
00:14:21,569 --> 00:14:26,073
[gloomy music playing]

210
00:14:26,156 --> 00:14:28,951
[reporters clamoring]

211
00:14:29,034 --> 00:14:32,162
Director Azuelo is not here.
He's in a meeting.

212
00:14:32,246 --> 00:14:34,832
- [overlapping chatter]
- You'll have to come back.

213
00:14:34,915 --> 00:14:36,208
Please, just come back next time.

214
00:14:36,292 --> 00:14:38,961
[overlapping chatter continues]

215
00:14:39,044 --> 00:14:42,047
[morose music playing]

216
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:54,059
- [chanting] Justice! Justice!
- [man] Get out of the way!

217
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:56,270
- [chanting continues]
- [man] Back off!

218
00:15:04,612 --> 00:15:05,863
[exhales heavily]

219
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:09,867
[unsettling music playing]

220
00:15:11,619 --> 00:15:13,037
How did he escape?

221
00:15:13,579 --> 00:15:14,830
Sabdani!

222
00:15:17,291 --> 00:15:18,125
So…

223
00:15:20,252 --> 00:15:22,463
Has the chief chewed you out already?

224
00:15:24,340 --> 00:15:27,760
You are such a screw-up, huh?

225
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:29,845
Not now, Montes.

226
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:34,350
I bet you let Datu Rahman escape.

227
00:15:34,433 --> 00:15:37,186
[tense music playing]

228
00:15:37,269 --> 00:15:39,563
I knew it.

229
00:15:45,402 --> 00:15:47,112
I didn't let Datu Rahman escape.

230
00:15:47,196 --> 00:15:50,240
I was transferring him
to another vehicle, as ordered.

231
00:15:50,324 --> 00:15:52,493
Yeah, right. [scoffs]

232
00:15:53,535 --> 00:15:55,663
No matter what you say,

233
00:15:55,746 --> 00:15:59,458
he still escaped under your custody.

234
00:16:00,042 --> 00:16:02,294
You freaking Muslims, huh?

235
00:16:02,378 --> 00:16:04,463
- [grunts]
- [thud]

236
00:16:04,546 --> 00:16:06,548
Hey! Cut it out!

237
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:08,968
Sir, he hit me first!

238
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:10,678
Unbelievable, Sabdani.

239
00:16:11,512 --> 00:16:15,099
You're already causing trouble
after the mess you made!

240
00:16:16,475 --> 00:16:17,685
This is your first warning.

241
00:16:18,686 --> 00:16:20,896
Next time, I'm going to suspend you!

242
00:16:20,980 --> 00:16:22,064
Sir.

243
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,607
Get out of my sight.

244
00:16:24,650 --> 00:16:25,859
Now!

245
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:30,489
[grim music playing]

246
00:16:42,710 --> 00:16:43,961
[Marcus] Director Azuelo.

247
00:16:44,044 --> 00:16:47,506
[tense music playing]

248
00:16:49,216 --> 00:16:50,926
What are you doing here?

249
00:16:51,010 --> 00:16:52,344
Sir…

250
00:16:52,928 --> 00:16:55,264
Sir, why did you tell the media

251
00:16:56,390 --> 00:16:59,351
that Datu Rahman escaped?
He did not escape!

252
00:17:01,103 --> 00:17:02,229
What are you saying?

253
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:04,648
- Sir.
- Have you really lost it?

254
00:17:04,732 --> 00:17:07,484
Sir, I was there. I saw what happened.

255
00:17:07,568 --> 00:17:09,403
Datu Rahman was abducted!

256
00:17:09,486 --> 00:17:10,738
Enough!

257
00:17:12,489 --> 00:17:13,741
Wait a minute.

258
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:17,953
What were you doing there?

259
00:17:18,037 --> 00:17:19,663
You're still suspended.

260
00:17:20,330 --> 00:17:22,291
Sir, I'm just trying to uncover the truth.

261
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:27,087
Because I want justice
for my comrades who lost their lives.

262
00:17:28,756 --> 00:17:31,759
Sir, they were your men, too.

263
00:17:32,801 --> 00:17:35,137
You should be doing everything
you can to catch the culprit.

264
00:17:36,513 --> 00:17:41,185
You are walking
on very thin ice, young man.

265
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:44,354
Do you even care,

266
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:46,190
or were you part of their deaths?

267
00:17:46,273 --> 00:17:48,025
[tense music swells]

268
00:17:48,108 --> 00:17:49,735
How dare you!

269
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,029
Alright, sir.

270
00:17:52,112 --> 00:17:54,114
I'll uncover the truth eventually.

271
00:17:57,993 --> 00:18:00,245
[Azuelo] Goddammit!

272
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:04,374
[tense music intensifies]

273
00:18:05,209 --> 00:18:07,002
[Jamillah] Father is missing!

274
00:18:07,086 --> 00:18:10,172
I can’t just stay on the island
and do nothing!

275
00:18:10,255 --> 00:18:11,548
I know!

276
00:18:12,382 --> 00:18:14,510
But the situation
is very dangerous, Jamillah!

277
00:18:14,593 --> 00:18:17,638
Father isn't just missing,
he’s been abducted!

278
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:20,516
That's why I'm here!

279
00:18:21,725 --> 00:18:23,143
To help you!

280
00:18:23,227 --> 00:18:25,270
Jamillah, I am dealing
with a lot of problems

281
00:18:25,354 --> 00:18:27,314
on top of searching for Father!

282
00:18:27,397 --> 00:18:29,024
Don't make things worse!

283
00:18:29,650 --> 00:18:32,152
Brother Jalil,
what do you think I'm doing?

284
00:18:33,862 --> 00:18:35,239
Being a burden?

285
00:18:35,322 --> 00:18:38,075
Jamillah, they massacred our community.

286
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:41,954
And the NLEA personnel who arrested Father

287
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:42,996
were killed as well.

288
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:48,043
We don’t know what
Father’s kidnappers are after.

289
00:18:48,127 --> 00:18:50,212
That's why I'm here.

290
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:53,215
To help you.

291
00:18:54,883 --> 00:18:57,219
[Jamillah sobbing softly]

292
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:04,935
Brother Jalil, you weren't
the only one who lost family.

293
00:19:06,061 --> 00:19:07,312
I did too!

294
00:19:09,523 --> 00:19:14,194
[Jamillah sobbing]

295
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:19,283
[somber music playing]

296
00:19:35,340 --> 00:19:37,342
[grunting]

297
00:19:37,426 --> 00:19:39,720
- [thud]
- [Jalil] <i>What do they want?</i>

298
00:19:40,721 --> 00:19:42,431
<i>Where did they take you, Father?</i>

299
00:19:42,514 --> 00:19:43,640
[tense music]

300
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:48,604
Do you know someone
who can access the CCTV camera here?

301
00:19:51,690 --> 00:19:53,150
Aren’t you supposed to be suspended?

302
00:19:53,233 --> 00:19:55,235
Dennis, even though I'm still suspended,

303
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:57,196
you still owe me.

304
00:19:57,279 --> 00:19:59,031
When are you going to let me go?

305
00:19:59,114 --> 00:20:00,782
[Marcus] <i>When I say so.</i>

306
00:20:02,326 --> 00:20:03,410
Come in.

307
00:20:04,494 --> 00:20:06,163
I'm sorry to disturb you.

308
00:20:06,246 --> 00:20:08,624
Oh, don't worry about it.

309
00:20:08,707 --> 00:20:12,127
Anything Mister Omar requests,
I’m happy to do.

310
00:20:12,211 --> 00:20:15,547
Besides, this is a piece of cake.

311
00:20:24,223 --> 00:20:25,224
Where'd they go?

312
00:20:26,225 --> 00:20:27,768
They disappeared.

313
00:20:28,435 --> 00:20:29,478
[Marcus] What happened?

314
00:20:30,646 --> 00:20:32,522
Why weren’t they caught
on the other cameras?

315
00:20:33,273 --> 00:20:34,149
Hold on.

316
00:20:35,067 --> 00:20:39,196
[tense music]

317
00:20:42,241 --> 00:20:44,660
[Marcus] <i>I tried to go after</i>
<i>the people who took him.</i>

318
00:20:44,743 --> 00:20:45,994
<i>But they opened fire.</i>

319
00:20:46,078 --> 00:20:46,954
- <i>Someone helped him escape.</i>
- [Sabdani] Hey!

320
00:20:48,705 --> 00:20:49,539
[grunts]
